RESULTS OF OPERATIONS
 
YEAR ENDED DECEMBER 31, 2011 COMPARED TO YEAR ENDED
DECEMBER 31, 2010
 
Sales
 
Our business for the year ended December 31, 2011 continued
to demonstrate robust growth.  Net sales increased by 71.9% from $370.5 million in 2010 to $637.1 million in 2011. This
growth was primarily driven by: (i) strong market demand for our CCA and copper wire products; (ii) the launch of the new smelting
capacity in the third quarter of 2010, which operated a full year in 2011 and allowed us to keep up with increased product demand;
(iii) the further increase in the smelting capacity in October 2011, and (iv) the increase of copper prices during 2011 relative
to 2010. Please see the table below for more details regarding the product sales breakdown by specific category.
 


  
