Average gross profit margin
decreased to 11.9% in 2011 as compared to 16.8% in 2010, primarily as a result of the addition of copper anode, which is a lower
margin product compared to the wire products. In addition, as a result of the copper wire capacity addition, copper wire products
sales have increased significantly as a percentage of total sales in 2011, when compared with fiscal year 2010.  Since
copper wire is a lower gross margin product than CCA wire, the increase in copper wire sales also contributed to the decrease in
average CCA and copper wire gross margin as well as overall gross margin.
 
